smartcard_list: add link to https://smartcard-atr.apdu.fr/
github action: use gcc for UCRT64

pcsc_scan; Windows can also use option -n

By default no ATR parser is defined on Windows.
So we do not need to have a special treatment. ATR parsing will be disabled by default.

Use Ctrl-C also on Windows

It works fine when UCRT64 environment is used instead of MSYS
https://www.msys2.org/docs/environments/
.gitignore: ignore generated files
configure.ac: statically link with pthread on Windows
configure.ac: log CFLAGS and CPPFLAGS variables

pcsc_scan: use LANG_USER_DEFAULT on Windows

LANG_USER_DEFAULT is a predefined value: The language of the current user.

pcsc_scan: define EX_* if sysexits.h is not available

sysexits.h is not available on MSYS2 UCRT64.

pcsc_scan: #include "config.h" first

We can now use HAVE_* defined in config.h to include, or not, other
header files.

configure: check for sysexits.h presence

MSYS2 UCRT64 does not provide this header.
Or maybe it is just mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-gcc.
